My babies closet, which I wanted to be the cutest place in the house got out of hand. It literally became a dumping ground and it made me sad everyday. So much so I avoided because I just couldn’t deal with it - and of course that just meant it kept getting worse

Thankfully I found the @homesort ladies🙏And I wanted to make this video for you to share how they helped me create systems so that it’s easier for me to stay organised. Because some of us are just a lil more messy than others🤷‍♀️ and that’s ok😬

But what wasn’t ok was that I let the mess infiltrate my self worth, I started to think I was a mess and let that bring me down and add to the already intense guilt of being a working mom and not having enough hours in the day 

I was hesitant to share all of this because I know there are far bigger issues in the world,  and I’m highly highly aware of my privileges, but if this can help even just one of you feeling this as a new mom in a pandemic or literally anyone feeling overwhelmed - you can ask for help and you’re doing great (virtual hug)🥰

Basically I can’t recommend the @homesort team enough and we love to support female founded companies, so give them a follow, you’ll be obsessed with all the tips, tricks and before and afters✨

#homeorganization #homesort #homeorganising #nurserydesign #nurseryinspiration #montessoriplayroom #montessoriinspired #montessoriathome #organizing #beforeandafterhomeedition

#AD| ❤️ In case you forgot, this is your reminder that you are indeed a badass, imperfectly perfect, more than enough, much needed human being

(Side note, I hope my Oscar winning performance gives you a good belly chuckle🤣)

For me it’s been all too easy to forget the great things about me, feel overwhelmed and some days I have to admit (mom guilt central) I miss the pre motherhood freedom and time I could carve out for myself uninterrupted

I quickly realised being a working mom during a pandemic I needed to ask for help. Even though we are told over and over by society that it’s a superpower to multi task, something has to give if you’re burnt out and overtired

I've been enjoying yummy @activiaus yogurts and have re prioritised moments for me throughout the week to feel realigned, recharged and proud of myself for knowing I’m worth it - and you are too!

So if this sounds like something you’d like to try, head over to @activiaus and start your journey💪

#activiaus #guthealth #wellbeing

node.text:
We are back @philipapayne for series 2 of Self Funding

Today we wanted to discuss how we are coping as new parents and chasing our careers. Part of me regrets not taking maternity leave but after feeling overwhelmed I took steps to balance baby and work and want to share how we do this together.

Philip has launched his podcast, educated himself on crypto and we have both diversified and grown our investment portfolios since the pandemic. As a partnership and individuals we realised the importance of constantly creating new goals and figuring out how to best support one another to achieve them.

As you know I got the amazing opportunity to partner with @activiaus an opportunity that fitted so well into my life as gut health has always been a priority of mine and it’s been one of the easiest ways I’ve taken care of myself when at times I’ve felt super burnt out or overwhelmed navigating motherhood because as they say you don’t just bring a baby into the world you also birth parents who have to figure it out too.

Hope you enjoy today’s episode and comment below any tips you have to balance your life as new patents or during this pandemic because I love learning from you!

.
.
.

#SelfFunding #momlife #newmom #parents #parenting #worklifebalance

node.text:
Last Monday @philipapayne and I went LIVE on IG & Tiktok to share some of our favorite partner exercises, but more importantly sharing how we show up and get to the actual workout together because that’s usually the hardest part😬

We are both pretttyyy competitive but we have to use that to challenge each other instead of discourage, and remind one another of how great we feel and all the positive benefits of moving💃

For us it’s important to share how we are feeling physically,🤰Post-partum is a whole other ball game, I definitely rely on philip to motivate me & push me. 

Communication is 🔑 when it comes to working out with your partner. 30 mins/day sounds reasonable but sometimes, after a long day, I have to tell philip I’m just way too tired 😂🤦‍♀️ & of course, he knows when to motivate or give me a lil boost & when to let me rest✌️😴

✏️Try planning & setting aside 30 mins to prioritize your wellness together as a ritual, whatever that looks like and see how you can support each other to help them achieve your well-being goals❤️

node.title: Self Funding: Ep 9 💪Working Out With Your Partner

node.text:
I look at my little one every day in awe and gratitude for every single cell in my being changed the day you came into our world. It was like meeting you and meeting the new me at the same time. 

And that transition came with challenges and expectations I constantly have to subdue and rewrite as I figure out what you, I, and your daddy need day-to-day.

I’m so grateful for all your support on my post about our breastfeeding journey and I wanted to share something @philipapayne got for me when I was struggling with increasing my milk supply - an Elvie pump.

He bought me the set and it was expensive $499!😬
But I used it everyday and loved it.
Somehow the brand or their PR ended up sending me a second one and I knew right away I wanted to gift it to one of you!

So for this week's giveaway, I will be giving away a set of Elvie Breast Pumps to one lucky momma🎉

◦◦◦◦◦◦◦◦◦◦

Just like last week…
HOW TO ENTER: 

1. Follow me on IG (let’s be friends)🥰
2. Reshare to your story and make sure to tag me💁🏼‍♀️
3. Tag 2 friends in the comments below❤️✨

Giveaway will be closed at 11:59pm CT 08/29/2021, and winners will be announced Monday on my story. Good luck!

◦◦◦◦◦◦◦◦◦◦

After wasting too many years being insecure, resentful and at war with my curves I wish I could show my younger self how far we’ve come 

I’ve mentioned before that jeans were a trigger for my body dysmorphia & ED. Trying on endless pairs that never fit my shape made me believe I was the problem, not the jeans. Now I know that our bodies are never the problem and thankfully times are changing! 

So here I am more confident in my skin than ever, at my largest size ever, modelling for the new @paige denim #FlauntYourPaige campaign😭
This means so much as I’ve loved the brand for so long🥰
Andddd it means even more because this whole new collection is specially created for our curves…

Nipped in waists with extra room for thighs and butts - I’m never getting jeans tailored again👌

posted some vids on my stories of these @paige fits, and will link them so you can shop the new collection

It also cracks me up because I shot all of these in my garage after my baby went to sleep, and my neighbours maybe, probably, definitely saw my knockers *awaits formal complaint from HOA*🙈 #worthit

#accessibility
Photo description: [Iskra created 3 looks for this shoot. Look 1 she’s wearing a blue vintage wash jean with black tee and bright yellow strappy heels with hair natural and loose. For this look she poses with a stool standing and seated smiling confidently. Look 2 is cheeky dark wash jean only and she faces away from camera posing with her arms then laying down like a curvy goddess. Look 3 is a classic black jean with a flowy white silk shirt that she wraps around her body and creates shapes to accentuate her curves. It’s hard to tell but all images were shot in her garage with natural light on a white background and the wall so have an imperfect feel]

node.text:
They say 1 whole year of breastfeeding is equivalent to a full time job the with the amount of hours… well it was a job I didn’t want to end, as challenging as it was at times especially establishing a consistent milk supply I cherished every second of it

I went in with rather an unrealistic expectation as my incredible momma breastfeed me for 4 years with ease and so when I lost my supply a few weeks in I was confused and felt like a failure

I’m beyond thankful for formula and not letting the pressure of “breast is best” make me feel like a terrible mom, because I needed to supplement and that worked so well for us

Never the less, even weeks after 13 month breast feeding journey came to an end I still started googling “can you restart your breast milk supply” “what’s the over the counter you can take to boost your supply” sometimes BF isn’t even about your baby it’s about you and the bond you fear to lose or for many are told you’ll never have, that’s such an awful pressure or expectation to place upon mother’s - your bond with your baby will be perfect no matter how you feed them, you are doing amazing no matter what that looks like for you❤️

How long or were you able to BF? I feel like the more parents I meet it makes me realise all journeys are you unique and you should never ever compare yours to someone else’s!🤍

#breastfeedingweek

node.text:
Let me preface this with I don’t believe in cancel culture. Period.

I’ve had many experiences in the fashion industry that have left me questioning if progress will ever happen across the board. And I’m in a white, able body, at a US size 12/14 I have the privilege of being able to shop in most stores. When I do get to work with a brand I usually have to ask are you ready to be more inclusive? 

These pics were taken at a store opening, not only are the clothes cute but I was looking forward to having the discussion of inclusion because there’s a limited size range which I’ve seen @katiesturino flag before (❤️u)

I believe supporting brands into improvement and growth rather than shaming and cancel culture because that feels to me the more positive route for change? But it doesn’t always work - let me know your thoughts!!!

After taking time out my day to go and support the opening I was told I could pick out a cute fit. It soon transpired  after searching the store my size was not available (again I know I’m very privileged as many have to assume their sizes won’t be carried and I get to assume mine is) long story short, I communicated that this was disappointing you’d chosen to invite me and I wanted to have a conversation with the team and even had my agency reach out so we could have a formal discussion of the importance of inclusion

Unfortunately after months of chasing to see if this managed to get noticed or flagged the one response received was “they are discussing it internally” aka they hope I’d go away and drop it?!

We all know staying silent doesn’t create change, I’m still learning how to hold brands accountable in a positive way so they want to do better, listen and learn

I’m speaking to a couple of brands atm who have said they want to and will be increasing sizing so pls brands don’t ignore inclusion, do it because it’s the right thing to do AND ITS GOOD FOR BUSINESS! Me and 67% of women size 14 or over want to wear your clothes!

Also I apologise if this felt at all “whiney” I don’t want to be insensitive to the many other issues going on rn❤️
